      "type": "policy",
      "name": "GIT-12: Auto-back-merge on release (MUST)",
      "definition": "A new rule appended to plugins/sulis/references/git-workflow-standard.md. States: every dev→main promotion MUST be followed by a back-integration of main to dev, performed by the release robot. Fast-forward when possible; PR when raced; never force-push dev.",
      "success_criterion": "The rule is appended in front-loaded order (after GIT-11), worded as MUST, includes a worked example covering both clean and raced paths.",
      "source": "user",
